Class ExistsIn<O,F,A>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.cqengine.query.simple.SimpleQuery<O,A>
      • com.googlecode.cqengine.query.simple.ExistsIn<O,F,A>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Query<O>

    public class ExistsIn<O,F,A>
extends SimpleQuery<O,A>
    Asserts than an object exists in a foreign collection, based on an attribute in the local collection being equal to an attribute in the foreign collection, and optionally with restrictions applied to objects in the foreign collection. This supports the equivalent of SQL EXISTS-type queries and JOINs between IndexedCollections.
    Since:
    2013-08-27 20:05
    Author:
    ngallagher
